:AntigoneEmotionMisery1 a :Emotion ;
  :description "Antigone laments being led in misery down her final path, unwept, unloved, and unwed." .

:AntigoneEmotionIsolation1 a :Emotion ;
  :description "Antigone feels abandoned: no friend grieves and no tears are wept for her fate." .

:AntigoneEmotionGriefForFamily1 a :Emotion ;
  :description "Antigone mourns her dead kin and speaks of joining them among the dead." .

:AntigoneEmotionCherishedHope1 a :Emotion ;
  :description "Antigone cherishes the thought that she will be dear to her father, mother, and brother in death." .

:AntigoneEmotionConfusionAboutGods1 a :Emotion ;
  :description "Antigone questions what holy law she violated and why she should still look to the gods when piety has brought a charge of impiety." .

:AntigoneEmotionResentmentAtUnjustJudgment1 a :Emotion ;
  :description "Antigone calls her judges unjust and wishes they suffer no more than she has suffered at their hands." .

:Antigone :experiencesEmotion :AntigoneEmotionMisery1, :AntigoneEmotionIsolation1, :AntigoneEmotionGriefForFamily1, :AntigoneEmotionCherishedHope1, :AntigoneEmotionConfusionAboutGods1, :AntigoneEmotionResentmentAtUnjustJudgment1 .

:CreonMotivationEnforceOrder1 a :Motivation ;
  :description "Creon intends Antigone be brought quickly and left alone, sealed in the tomb, as he ordered." .

:CreonMoralDecisionEntombAntigone1 a :MoralDecision ;
  :description "Creon orders Antigone sealed alone in a shadowy tomb, claiming their hands are clean and that the decision of death or living entombed is hers." .

:Creon :hasMotivation :CreonMotivationEnforceOrder1 ;
  :makesMoralDecision :CreonMoralDecisionEntombAntigone1 .

:AntigoneMotivationHonorPolyneices1 a :Motivation ;
  :description "Antigone honored Polyneices by burying him and claims this is her 'reward' for that act." .

:AntigoneMotivationJoinFamilyInDeath1 a :Motivation ;
  :description "Antigone goes to the tomb as an everlasting home to join her own among the dead." .

:Antigone :hasMotivation :AntigoneMotivationHonorPolyneices1, :AntigoneMotivationJoinFamilyInDeath1 .

:EthicalPrincipleKinHonorAboveAll1 a :EthicalPrinciple ;
  :description "Antigone asserts a 'law' by which she honors her brother above all others, since she can never have a new brother once her parents are in Hades." .

:EthicalPrinciplePietyReverence1 a :EthicalPrinciple ;
  :description "Pious/reverent behavior and prayer are invoked as right conduct, though it is said to be intolerable to those in power." .

:Antigone :advocatesFor :EthicalPrincipleKinHonorAboveAll1, :EthicalPrinciplePietyReverence1 .
:Chorus :advocatesFor :EthicalPrinciplePietyReverence1 .

:ConflictPietyVsPower1 a :Conflict ;
  :description "Reverent prayers/piety are said to be intolerable to those in power, implying a clash between piety and political authority." ;
  :conflictBetween :EthicalPrinciplePietyReverence1, :Creon .

:ConflictPietyAccusedAsImpiety1 a :Conflict ;
  :description "Antigone says pious behavior has incurred the charge of impiety, creating a contradiction between her intent and the accusation." ;
  :conflictBetween :EthicalPrinciplePietyReverence1, :Antigone .

:ConflictKinLawVsCreonJudgment1 a :Conflict ;
  :description "Antigone claims she honored Polyneices well by a higher 'law,' but Creon deems her action wrong and reckless." ;
  :conflictBetween :EthicalPrincipleKinHonorAboveAll1, :CreonMoralDecisionEntombAntigone1 .

