:AntigoneMotivationHonorPolyneices1 :relatedTo :CreonMoralDecisionEntombAntigone1 .

:ThemePowerVsPiety1 a :Theme ;
  :description "Political power rejects or punishes reverent prayer and pious conduct." .

:ThemeFamilyLoyaltyAndBurialRites1 a :Theme ;
  :description "Loyalty to kin and the duty of burial/funeral rites are treated as overriding obligations." .

:ThemeIsolationAndUnmournedDeath1 a :Theme ;
  :description "Antigone faces death without marriage, friends, or public mourning, emphasizing abandonment." .

:ThemeDivineJusticeAndHumanJudgment1 a :Theme ;
  :description "Antigone questions whether the gods approve and calls human judges unjust, invoking the possibility of divine reckoning." .

:ThemeLivingEntombment1 a :Theme ;
  :description "The punishment of being sealed alive in a tomb blurs life and death and frames the tomb as a 'bridal chamber'." .

